article_title: Fed Given Green Light by Pay Prospects
article_text:
The Federal Reserve may finally be getting the better wage growth it has long been looking for. But having waited so long, investors shouldn’t expect it to stand in the way of letting American workers’ paychecks fatten some more.

The Fed on Wednesday kept its target range on overnight rates steady at zero to 0.25%, but clearly indicated it doesn’t expect rates to stay there much longer. In its postmeeting statement, the Fed noted...
